========================================================
Round Robin
========================================================
Preemptive. Each ready process gets at most quantum=3 time units per turn. Arrivals at a time-slice boundary are queued before the preempted process.

Execution timeline:
  [ 0,  3)  IDLE
  [ 3,  6)  P1
  [ 6,  7)  P1
  [ 7, 10)  IDLE
  [10, 12)  P2
  [12, 15)  P3

Compact Gantt view:
  |0 IDLE |3 P1 |6 P1 |7 IDLE |10 P2 |12 P3 |15

Per-process results:
Process        Arr   Burst    Prio  Deadline  FirstStart    Finish   Waiting  Turnaround  Response   Missed
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
P1               3       4       2        12           3         7         0           4         0       no
P2              10       2       1        15          10        12         0           2         0       no
P3              11       3       3        20          12        15         1           4         1       no

Summary metrics:
  Makespan              : 15
  Total busy time       : 9
  CPU utilization       : 60.00%
  Throughput            : 0.20 processes/unit-time
  Average waiting time  : 0.33
  Average turnaround    : 3.33
  Average response time : 0.33
  Deadline misses       : 0 / 3


==================== POLICY COMPARISON ====================
Policy                              Avg Wait  Avg Turnaround      Avg Resp    Misses      Util %
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FCFS - First Come First Served          0.33            3.33          0.33         0       60.00
SJF - Shortest Job First                0.33            3.33          0.33         0       60.00
Priority Scheduling                     0.33            3.33          0.33         0       60.00
Round Robin                             0.33            3.33          0.33         0       60.00

Interpretation hints:
  - Lower waiting/turnaround time is usually better for batch-style workloads.
  - Lower response time is important for interactive workloads.
  - Round Robin often improves response time, but can increase turnaround time.
  - Deadline misses show whether a policy is suitable for time-bound workloads.
